    <h1>Asia TV Fo&#xAD;rum Pitches (Ad&#xAD;vi&#xAD;sory: 16 years and above)</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200911/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-11"><time>2020-09-11</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>The Asia TV Fo­rum (ATF) is call­ing for pitches from Asian con­tent mak­ers to be de­vel­oped within or out­side of the re­gion. Fi­nal­ists stand to win cash prizes to de­velop their win­ning con­cept or earn op­por­tu­ni­ties to have their script scouted and pur­chased. There are three main pitch pro­grammes – ATF Chi­nese Pitch, ATF An­i­ma­tion Pitch and ATF For­mats Pitch – which are open to in­di­vid­u­als, stu­dents, free­lancers and com­pa­nies. ATF, part of the Singapore Me­dia Fes­ti­val, con­nects in­flu­en­tial play­ers in the en­ter­tain­ment con­tent in­dus­try across all gen­res and plat­forms.</p>
    <p>For ATF An­i­ma­tion & For­mats Pitches, sub­mit by Sept 30. For ATF Chi­nese Pitch, sub­mit by Sept 28</p>
    <p>Free bit.ly/3bG7IKf</p>


